HEADWORD: Hemautography
<hw>Hem`au*tog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The obtaining of a curve similar to a pulse
curve or sphygmogram by allowing the blood from a divided artery to
strike against a piece of paper.</def></p>

